Teach your family about cybersecurity topic of your choice.

In this activity, I explained basic cybersecurity concepts to a family member. I chose to talk about phishing attacks.

I explained how phishing messages usually try to trick users into clicking on suspicious links or providing personal information. I also showed examples of how these messages can look like legitimate emails or texts.

I advised them to always check the sender, avoid clicking unknown links, and not share sensitive information online.

This activity helped me realise that many people are not fully aware of cybersecurity risks, and simple knowledge can help prevent attacks.
